OL,3,C'The pitch was immaculate': Everton
OL,4,Cgroundsman retires after 38 years
OL,6,FEverton Football Club's legendary head
OL,7,Fgroundsman has officially retired
OL,8,Fafter an extraordinary 38-year career
OL,9,Fkeeping pitches "immaculate".
OL,11,FBob Lennon clocked off for the final
OL,12,Ftime on Friday, 29 May, bringing to an
OL,13,Fend nearly four decades of dedication
OL,14,Fto the Toffees across both the
OL,15,FBellefield training ground and
OL,16,FGoodison Park.
OL,18,FReflecting on his departure, the 66-
OL,19,Fyear-old said: "I've got no regrets. I
OL,20,Fthink it's my time to finish now.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/4
